🛠️ Installation & Setup
Prerequisites
Make sure you have Node.js installed on your machine.

Execution Steps
Clone or extract this project folder into your local working directory.

Open your terminal or command prompt and navigate to the project directory:

Bash
cd path/to/zombie-shooter
Install the development web server dependencies:

Bash
npm install
Fire up the local secure-context development environment:

Bash
npm run dev
Your browser should instantly launch http://localhost:3000 (or http://127.0.0.1:3000).

⚠️ Critical Camera Permissions Note
Since webcams strictly require a Secure Context, you must always run the project through localhost or 127.0.0.1. Clicking the index.html file directly from a file directory will prevent the camera from initializing. Be sure to hit "Allow" when the web browser requests camera access!

⚡ Tech Stack
Core Engine: Vanilla HTML5 Canvas 2D API

AI Processing: MediaPipe Hands Model v0.4

Style Preprocessor: Native CSS Custom Properties (Variables) & Keyframe Engines

Environment Server: Live Server Ecosystem (ES Module Compliant Native CORS)
